newsitem.title: MALAYSIA: Malaysia's December palm oil exports 717,197t - SGS.
newsitem.headline: Malaysia's December palm oil exports 717,197t - SGS.

text.p: Cargo surveyor Societe Generale de Surveillance (SGS) Malaysia Sdn Bhd said it estimated Malaysia's palm oil exports for December at 717,197 tonnes against 700,566 tonnes in November.
It said the exports comprised 216,995 tonnes of RBD palm oil, 244,663 tonnes of RBD palm olein and 72,983 tonnes of RBD palm stearin.
China, which was the main buyer during the period, taking 106,400 tonnes, Pakistan 85,190 tonnes, India 68,722 tonnes and Japan 50,937 tonnes.
Countries in the European Union bought 120,212 tonnes.
